radiographic_examinations.findings: Confirmed subarachnoid hemorrhage (SAH), Grade II on the World Federation of Neurosurgical Societies scale and Grade 1 on the Fisher scale.
Large complex right proximal middle cerebral artery (MCA) aneurysm and a smaller right distal MCA aneurysm, an aneurysm at the basilar tip, and another on the superior cerebellar artery.

Heavy calcification with 50% narrowing of both common carotid arteries just proximal to the carotid artery bulbs; common femoral, external iliac, and internal iliac arteries were patent bilaterally but reduced caliber; aortoiliac occlusion extending from below the origin of the internal mesenteric artery to the external iliac artery origins bilaterally.
The treated aneurysms are stable, and the untreated distal MCA aneurysm remains unchanged in size and configuration.
